From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Wed, 17 Jun 2026 14:45:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] misc: wait after Fruit Jam usbhost reset release

The active USB host probes released reset and then waited only 100 us before
reconfiguring PIO, sending SOFs, and starting control transfers.  Full-speed
devices, especially the onboard hub at the Fruit Jam root port, need normal
USB reset recovery time before they are required to answer endpoint-zero
traffic.

Add an explicit 25 ms reset-recovery delay after releasing SE0.  This keeps
the small diagnostic stack simple while avoiding setup transactions that begin
before the root hub has finished reset recovery.
---
 drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
--- a/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
+++ b/drivers/misc/fruitjam_usbhost.c
@@ -54,6 +54,7 @@
 #define FJ_USBHOST_DMA_TIMEOUT_US	2000u
 #define FJ_USBHOST_SOF_BURST_FRAMES	20u
 #define FJ_USBHOST_ACTIVE_RESET_MS	50u
+#define FJ_USBHOST_RESET_RECOVERY_MS	25u
 #define FJ_USBHOST_BOOT_KEYBOARD_ADDR	1u
 #define FJ_USBHOST_BOOT_KEYBOARD_CONFIG	1u
 #define FJ_USBHOST_BOOT_KEYBOARD_EP	1u
@@ -3252,7 +3253,8 @@ static int fj_usbhost_pio_reset_active(struct fruitjam_usbhost *uh)
 	fj_usbhost_bus_reset_override(uh, true);
 	msleep(FJ_USBHOST_ACTIVE_RESET_MS);
 	fj_usbhost_bus_reset_override(uh, false);
-	udelay(100);
+	msleep(FJ_USBHOST_RESET_RECOVERY_MS);
+
 	ret = fj_usbhost_pio_configure_sms(uh);
 	if (ret)
 		return ret;
